<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Re: A Correction of Geiger - Actually I meant what I said.</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Geiger">Geiger</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 11:55 a.m. 11/2/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Re: A Correction of Geiger - Actually I meant what I said.<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=710" TARGET=_self>A Correction of Geiger</A> (Platinum)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>The game doesn't inherently support mindless killing. The PvP server will be the only server without a lvl Cap. That will curb a great deal of killing. The game was designed around PvE and Roleplaying. PvP wasn't quite what would be termed an "Afterthought" but it has a great deal of potential to improve. If you were to go on the -PvP server you would not find anything remotely close to UO. The PvP server however is open to that behavoir and I'm working on ways of dealing with it.

<P>Geiger
<P>&gt; I read this quote of yours "This game doesn't inherently
<BR>&gt; support sensless killing" and feel the need to correct it
<BR>&gt; in light of my opinions. First off, yes, EverQuest highly
<BR>&gt; promotes random pk'ng. The switch allows only two types of
<BR>&gt; players, -pvp and +pvp. A +pvp can kill everyone, thats just how
<BR>&gt; it is right now whether you are on a pvp server or not. If the
<BR>&gt; restrictions on players on a pvp server become so great, many
<BR>&gt; will go2 -pvp servers, turn on pvp, and just hope they encounter
<BR>&gt; other pvp players. EverQuest at the moment IS NOT a solid
<BR>&gt; atmosphere. The game is not solid enough to say 'ok pvp server
<BR>&gt; do what you want, game will handle' (although it is a beta).
<BR>&gt; Right now power of gm's is still required to keep players
<BR>&gt; actions in line. Whether there is +pvp, -pvp, rules, gm's etc
<BR>&gt; there will still be what are known as "fuqsters",
<BR>&gt; players that only seek the destruction of others. And whether or
<BR>&gt; not they are on a pvp server, believe me if UO is any
<BR>&gt; indication, they will find a way to mess up someone else, screw
<BR>&gt; someone's character, and generally cause havoc. The answer is to
<BR>&gt; create a solid pvp environment, that doesn't rely on other
<BR>&gt; players "role playing" because pk is VERY MUCH
<BR>&gt; roleplaying. Sitting in town hitting "fish" a bunch of
<BR>&gt; times is not role playing, its mindless drone activity.
<BR>&gt; Futhermore, there should also not be so many rules on a pvp
<BR>&gt; server that limit pvp. Players on a PvP server fully understand
<BR>&gt; what they are getting into. Were it up to me I would ask players
<BR>&gt; to design their own version of PvP, then at least I would know
<BR>&gt; what players truely want.
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
